107.text: Addex Therapeutics , a biotechnology company based in Geneva , Switzerland

269.text: Charles Blanke , an oncologist at Oregon Health & Science University in Portland and leader of the publicly funded SWOG Cancer Research Network

112.text: Tim Dyer , chief executive of Addex Therapeutics , a biotechnology company based in Geneva , Switzerland

quotes.text: "I can't even put into words what we've been able to do to get to this point,"
quotes.speaker: her

quotes.text: "My kids have given bone biopsies; I gave up my job and moved to a new country. We've just been going, going, going."
quotes.speaker: her

quotes.text: "My son asks me all the time, 'So when are we doing this trial? When can I? I don't want to feel this pain anymore,'"
quotes.speaker: Unknown

quotes.text: "I feel like we were chugging along on a train and then somebody dropped a huge boulder on it."
quotes.speaker: Addex

quotes.text: "We're going to see a nearly complete close-down in clinical research,"
quotes.speaker: Tim Dyer

quotes.text: "The health-care systems will simply be overloaded."
quotes.speaker: Tim Dyer

quotes.text: "We are now seeing impacts on clinical-trial continuity in all the regions where we conduct clinical studies."
quotes.speaker: Addex

quotes.text: "It's hard to believe that just a month ago, I'd never seen cancer clinical trials better,"
quotes.speaker: Herbst

quotes.text: "Now the whole process has really ground to a halt, and I feel bad because there are patients who might have benefited from those trials."
quotes.speaker: Herbst

quotes.text: "Did we do enough thinking in advance in terms of how research would be affected? My answer is no, we didn't,"
quotes.speaker: his

quotes.text: "And whether that delay manifests in delaying final approvals is unknowable today."
quotes.speaker: Bierer

quotes.text: "Our lives have always been in panic mode,"
quotes.speaker: Nizar

quotes.text: "Now the world has a glimpse into what our reality is."
quotes.speaker: Unknown
